        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): avoid silent polling drops for in-flight updates",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #44930 by tightening Telegram polling restart durability so an update accepted by the runner cannot be silently lost when Telegram-side offset acknowledgement gets ahead of OpenClaw handler completion.\n\n## Plan\n\n- Add or adjust a durable accepted/in-flight update record before the polling runner can confirm newer offsets to Telegram.\n- On restart, reconcile persisted accepted/in-flight state with the last completed watermark so still-unprocessed updates are either replay-safe or surfaced with explicit recovery logging instead of disappearing silently.\n- Keep the existing duplicate/replay guards from #46674/#59331 intact; this fix is about lost updates, not duplicate closeout.\n- Add regression coverage for a two-update batch where the second update is accepted by grammY, the process restarts before handler completion, and the message is not silently dropped.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/polling-session.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-core.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n\n## Credit\n\nReported by @nox-openclaw in #44930, with code-path analysis from @dsantoreis in the issue thread.\n\nProjectClownfish replacement details:\n- Cluster: ghcrawl-191453-agentic-merge\n- Source PRs: none\n- Credit: Credit @nox-openclaw for the #44930 silent-drop report.; Credit @dsantoreis for the hydrated #44930 code-path analysis distinguishing the Telegram-side offset confirmation race from local watermark persistence.; Mention #739 and #46674 only as historical context; do not claim #44930 is a duplicate of those closed issues.\n- Validation: pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/polling-session.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-core.test.ts; pnpm check:changed\n",
